-- Ecuador Bank Lending Rose to $12.9 Billion in December, SBS Says
-- B y   N a t h a n   G i l l
-- 2012-01-17T20:56:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-17/ecuador-bank-lending-rose-to-12-9-billion-in-december-sbs-says.html
Ecuador’s private banks increased
their total outstanding loans to $12.9 billion in December while
deposits rose to $19 billion, the South American nation’s
banking regulator said today in a report on its website.  Private banks had $10.7 billion in loans and deposits of
$16.6 billion a year earlier, according to data from the
Superintendent of Banks, the country’s bank regulator known as
the SBS.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nathan Gill in Quito at 
